com.fasterxml.storemate.backend.leveldb

Class LevelDBStoreBackend

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.storemate.store.backend.StoreBackend
      • com.fasterxml.storemate.backend.leveldb.LevelDBStoreBackend

  • public class LevelDBStoreBackend
extends StoreBackend
    StoreBackend implementation that uses Java LevelDB implementation. Note that per-entry locking is assumed to be provided by caller; no attempt is made to synchronize individual operations at store level.

      • upsertEntry

        public boolean upsertEntry(StorableKey key,
                  Storable newEntry,
                  OverwriteChecker checker,
                  AtomicReference<Storable> oldEntryRef)
                    throws IOException,
                           StoreException
        Description copied from class: StoreBackend
        Method that may insert (if no entry with given key exists) or try to overwrite an entry with given key; but overwrite only happens if given 'checker' object allows overwrite. It should only be called if overwrite is truly conditional; otherwise other methods (like StoreBackend.putEntry(com.fasterxml.storemate.shared.StorableKey, com.fasterxml.storemate.store.Storable)} or StoreBackend.ovewriteEntry(StorableKey, Storable)) are more efficient.
        Specified by:
        upsertEntry in class StoreBackend
        oldEntryRef - If not null, existing entry will be returned via this object
        Returns:
        True if entry was created or updated; false if not (an old entry exists, and checker did not allow overwrite)
        Throws:
        IOException
        StoreException
